title: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Body-Worn and Dash Camera Footage – Arrest of Alexis T. Trent (April 25, 2024)

communications.subject: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Body-Worn and Dash Camera Footage – Arrest of Alexis T. Trent (April 25, 2024)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, Chapter 119, I respectfully request copies of all body-worn camera (BWC) and vehicle dash camera footage related to the arrest of Alexis T. Trent (DOB: 12/31/1969) on or about April 25, 2024 near 4000 Sombrero Boulevard, Marathon, Monroe County, FL.

Specifically, I am requesting:

All body-worn camera footage recorded by any Monroe County Sheriff's Office personnel during the initial stop, field sobriety testing, detention, arrest, and transport of Alexis T. Trent.

All dash camera footage from any patrol vehicles involved in the stop, detention, or transport.

Please include footage captured shortly before, during, and immediately after the incident. I understand the listed booking time is 9:54 PM; therefore, I request responsive footage from approximately 8:30 PM to 11:30 PM on April 25, 2024.

If portions of the requested footage are exempt or confidential, please produce the non-exempt portions and cite the specific legal exemptions justifying any withholding or redaction.

I am willing to pay any reasonable fees for duplication and labor but request notification if the costs will exceed $50. Please provide the requested records in an electronic format if possible.

Thank you for your time and assistance.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Police Cam News

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Arizona Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

1. A copy of any policy concerning recognition or registration of student organizations at your institution or at any institution within your district.

2. A copy of any list of active or recognized student organizations at your institution or at any institution within your district.

title: Records Request - Eads and 18th STreet South

communications.subject: Virginia Freedom of Information Act Request: Records Request - Eads and 18th STreet South
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

For the multifamily property known as Crystal Towers and Crytal Flats located at 1600 South Eads Street and 505 18th Street South Arlington VA 22202 with Parcel ID 5-011-010, 35-011-011, 35-011-001, please provide the following information:

Notice and summary of any open/outstanding zoning, building, and/or fire code violations, or written confirmation that none currently exist;
Copies of Certificates of Occupancy, or if none are available, please state the reason for their absence and whether the lack of Certificates of Occupancy will result in any enforcement action; and
Copies of any zoning approval documents, specifically a copy of the Crystal Towers Site Plan #13 and 1720 S Eads Street Site Plan #424

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Olivia James.

Any of the following documents submitted by Champlain Valley Educational Services (CVES), BEDS Code: 099000000000, to the NYSED Office of Facilities Planning from January 1, 1980, through March 28, 2025:

#1 - Letters of Intent (LOIs) / PRELIMINARY SUBMISSIONS: All LOIs submitted by CVES for proposed capital projects during this time period. These records should include:
  - The full text of each Letter of Intent.
  - Any associated documents or attachments submitted alongside the LOIs.

#2 - Certificates of Substantial Completion: All Certificates of Substantial Completion submitted by CVES for capital projects completed during this time period. These records should include:

y10n

communications.subject: RE: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: CVES capital projects
communications.communication:
Dear y10n:

This is to acknowledge receipt of your Freedom of Information Law (FOIL) request for State Education Department (SED) records regarding Champlain Valley Educational Services. The reference number for this request is FL-EM-25/374.   Please be advised that you will hear further from the Department by approximately April 28, 2025 as to whether your request will be granted or denied in whole or in part.

SED charges the statutorily permitted fees under FOIL. These include $.25 per page for photocopies or the actual cost of reproducing records requested under FOIL (Public Officers Law §87[1][b][iii]). Payment must be made to the NYS Education Department by check or money order. Do not send any payment until you are notified that your request is granted and informed of the charge for your request. If your request is granted, the records will be provided to you in the manner requested (i.e. hardcopy or electronic), or if not specified, in a reasonable manner selected by this office.

If your request is granted, and there is a fee, one of the following will happen:

1. If your request can be filled immediately, and the total photocopy or reproduction fee is under $25.00, staff will forward the requested records to you with a statement what you owe. Or:

2. If the reproduction fee or photocopy fee for your request is $25.00 or more, you will be advised of the page count (+100 pages) or other expenses and the fee(s) owed in advance of our providing the records. Upon receipt of payment, staff will photocopy or otherwise reproduce the requested records and transmit, as appropriate. Or:

3. If it will take time to locate and/or photocopy or otherwise reproduce the records you have requested, you will be given a date by which you will be provided with a page count and/or estimated cost to fulfil your request.

Please note, there is no provision in law or regulation requiring the waiver of a fee under FOIL.
Regards,
Records Access Officer

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Hello, 

I am requesting copies of contracts with the city of Stanton. 

Records should include memorandum of understandings and contracts
Copies of financial obligations, budgets, and other data related to costs, funding, and expenses
Any policies written specifically for Stanton

Please search from 2018 to 2024. 

Thank you

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Joey Scott

communications.subject: RE: California Public Records Act Request: OCSD MOU
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

I wanted to follow up on the following California Public Records Act request, copied below, and originally submitted on April 15, 2025. Please let me know when I can expect to receive a response.

Thanks for your help, and let me know if further clarification is needed.

communications.subject: CPRA - 13040.Scott // City of Stanton
communications.communication:
Good Morning Mr. Scott,

The Orange County Sheriff’s Department (OCSD) has identified responsive records, which are still under review. The OCSD anticipates making the records available to you on or before Monday, May 12, 2025. Nothing in this email should be construed as a representation that the OCSD has all of the records requested or that the OCSD is waiving any exemptions available under the PRA.

Thank you,

Luke Schnekenburger
Orange County Sheriff’s Department
Records Division
(714) 834-3223

communications.subject: CPRA - 13040.Scott // City of Stanton
communications.communication:
Good Afternoon Mr. Scott,

Please see the attached records that are responsive to your request. Regarding “any policies written specifically for Stanton,” the Orange County Sheriff's Department has no records responsive to your request

Respectfully,

Luke Schnekenburger
Orange County Sheriff’s Department
Records Division
(714) 834-3223
